"Saini R., Majhi M.C., Kapoor R., Kumar A., Kumar R.","CSD, a database of microbial strains for carbon fixation",2009,"Environmental Modelling and Software","24","9",,"1133","1134",,,10.1016/j.envsoft.2009.02.016,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-65649115901&partnerID=40&md5=85fd8ed5cc78c9e4561f833082a62940","Institute of Genomics and Integrative Biology, Mall Road, New Delhi, 110007, India; Department Botany, Delhi University, New Delhi, 110007, India","Saini, R., Institute of Genomics and Integrative Biology, Mall Road, New Delhi, 110007, India; Majhi, M.C., Institute of Genomics and Integrative Biology, Mall Road, New Delhi, 110007, India; Kapoor, R., Department Botany, Delhi University, New Delhi, 110007, India; Kumar, A., Institute of Genomics and Integrative Biology, Mall Road, New Delhi, 110007, India; Kumar, R., Institute of Genomics and Integrative Biology, Mall Road, New Delhi, 110007, India","The CSD database contains a list of microorganisms involved in biological fixation of carbon dioxide. The database allows managing of information related to carbon dioxide fixation utilizing microbes belonging to four different classes i.e. microorganisms, genus listing, mechanisms and literature. The database can help in devising biological strategies for reducing carbon dioxide from the environment. It can also serve as comprehensive knowledgebase to search the microbes capable of utilizing carbon dioxide. © 2009 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Biological fixation; Carbon dioxide utilizing strain database; CO2 fixing pathways; CSD; Global warming","Biological fixation; Carbon dioxide fixations; Carbon fixations; CO2 fixing pathways; CSD; Knowledge-base; Microbial strains; Global warming; Microorganisms; Strain; Carbon dioxide; carbon dioxide; carbon fixation; database; global warming; microbial activity",,,,,,"Bruce, E.R., Opportunities for renewable bioenergy using microorganisms (2008) Biotechnology and Bioengineering, 100 (2), pp. 203-212;